Subject: RE: Car EMI Rent Problem
Body:
From: Kumar, Ram (Cognizant) 
Sent: Thursday, September 14, 2017 17:29
To: JK, Vishal Rathnam (Cognizant) <VishalRathnam.JK@cognizant.com>
Subject: Car EMI Rent Problem

 

 Write a program that figures the monthly car payment using this formula:

 

payment = (rate + rate / (1 + rate)^months – 1 ) * amount where rate is the annual rate divided by 1,200 (that is, 6 % has rate = .005) and the carat character means “raised to the power of.” The syntax to use the power function is

 

Math.Pow(val, power)

Subject: Re: Opportunity in EAS
Body:
Hi,




The only reason I'm seeing not to take up this opportunity is the cost of living in Bangalore . I cannot manage to afford relocating this year as i have taken a loan which requires that i pay 65% of my monthly compensation as monthly installment until the end of this year . And it's really hard to manage with the remaining 35% of my salary in a city like Bangalore . I hope you understand my situation .




However, if you really think that i should not pass up this opportunity , please let me know your thoughts . I would be willing to reconsider my decision . Thanks .




Regards

Hi All,

 

As you may be aware, Europe’s new privacy law, known as the General Data Protection Regulation or GDPR, comes into force effective May 2018.  The GDPR introduces extensive changes regarding the handling of information relating to individuals and applies to both customers and service providers.

 

As part of this compliance initiative , we are supposed to complete the  below e-learning which gives a high-level introduction to the General Data Protection Regulation, focused on what the law is and its business impact. This short eLearning course is recommended for all Cognizant associates.

 

https://cognizant-console.lrn.com/learn/preview?curriculumId=-1&moduleId=24408&systemId=44452  (Works best in Chrome)

 

Requesting managers to drive this and share the course completion status in the sheet attached for your respective associates. Please revert for clarifications if any 

 

Regards,

Priya

 

From: Privacy(Cognizant) 
To: Cognizant ALL (Global) <COGALLGL@cognizant.com <mailto:COGALLGL@cognizant.com> >
Subject: Six Months… Are you Ready? Countdown to GDPR

 

 



 

The GDPR countdown continues …only 6 months left to go! 

 

The GDPR comes into force on 25 May 2018 and will impact all business teams and corporate functions globally.  We have been working hard, but with the deadline looming, how will you ensure you are GDPR ready in time?

 

How does GDPR impact me? 

GDPR compliance is the responsibly of all Cognizant associates so you need to ensure you are aware of your responsibilities. Take the ‘Short Introduction to GDPR <https://cognizant-console.lrn.com/learn/preview?curriculumId=-1&moduleId=24408&systemId=44452> ’ training, as well as the specific training available on the GDPR microsite <https://compliance.cognizant.com/Privacy> , to understand the key impacts of GDPR and what you need to do.

 

How can I make sure my client account is GDPR ready? 

Follow the checklist for every account and take the Gap Analysis training, available on the GDPR microsite <https://compliance.cognizant.com/Privacy>  to understand where you are today compared to where you need to be by May 2018. 

 

I work in a corporate function – do I have to do anything?

Corporate functions also have to prepare for GDPR and more details will be issued shortly. In the meantime, check out the GDPR microsite <https://compliance.cognizant.com/Privacy>  which has information and for corporate functions.

 

Create GDPR opportunities! 

Our clients need to become GDPR compliant too. Get in touch with our CBC AIM team at gdprteam@cognizant.com <mailto:gdprteam@cognizant.com>  to learn about the GDPR related services we can offer our clients. 

 

Visit the GDPR microsite <https://compliance.cognizant.com/Privacy>  now for lots of training, guidance and templates to help with your GDPR compliance efforts.  Questions?  Contact the Privacy team at privacy@cognizant.com <mailto:privacy@cognizant.com> .

 

Are you a GDPR guru or a GDPR beginner? Test your knowledge now! Take our quick quiz <https://www.yammer.com/cognizant.com/#/threads/inGroup?type=in_group&feedId=11008596&view=unviewed>  to see how well you know GDPR.

Subject: Plans to pursue higher studies
Body:
Hi Monisha,

 

Hope you are doing good. I have been trying to set up a meeting with you to inform you of this in person, but you were unavailable.

I am going to do my masters in Business administration this year and hence I will submitting my resignation once I have depleted all my earned leaves(Vacation and comp off).

This communication email is to keep you informed that I will be availing my compensatory off leaves this week(26th June to 28th June), and my vacation leave from next week(8 days).

Once I have used up all my vacation leaves and compensatory off I will submit my resignation in people soft HCM.

Hope the transition is smooth.

 

Warm Regards,

Vishal Rathnam JK

Programmer Analyst

Subject: RE: Request to apply comp off leave for June 28th as I'm on notice period
Body:
Hi Anand/Monisha,

 

I had already spoken with you about my disinterest in the work carried out in this project and more specifically by my team on the beginning of April month.

I’ve said that this work here is of no growth to me and I feel like working at an Non-Voice BPO project rather than an IT project. One of the major reasons for me submitting my resignation is the quality of the nature of the work being done here is sub-par. I have been trained as a dotnet full stack developer and I will not continue to do such trivial work being assigned to me here. I will only carry out work that is done by a full stack developer. If you feel that I’m following the trend of being unproductive it is because the work being assigned to me is trivial. I don’t find working in a spreadsheet, monitoring abends and creating documents for requesting jobs as interesting. I am capable of far more challenging work than that and willing to learn any new technology to carry out said such challenging work. My role here is not allowing me to do that. I’m the kind of person who clocks in extra time without being asked if I find the work I’m doing is interesting, but the case here is I’m kind of being coerced into working more than 9 hours and on weekends too. For me project standards, personal and career growth are of far greater value than money, and none of my expectations are even remotely met here. If you’re considering converting the days I’ve clocked in from last Thursday (7/12) as LOP, please go ahead and convert the remainder of Notice period as LOP too.

 

Thank you,

Vishal Rathnam JK

Programmer Analyst

Subject: A Huge loss befalls Cognizant
Body:
September 7th, 2018. Cognizant is losing its most pivotal resource in history. I bestow upon you,

my underlings, this opportunity to showcase your skills and keep Cognizant afloat in my absence.

 

I've never been one for cheesy words and emotional goodbyes, but I feel like some things have to be said.

My time here of 20 months have given me memories to cherish and moments with people that I'll be 

wistful of over the years to come. I have learnt a lot from each of you as have each of you from me.

Some of the best times of my life that I had, I had it with you people.

 

My time in Mainframe training is an unforgettable experience to me. We had the best trainer who understood

us. We used to enjoy coming to work on Saturdays. The times we had playing truth or dare, all the 

chats, playing UNO, carrom all seem like they just happened. Our trip to MGM was the one which most of us had 

come and I know how hard it was to get the ones coming to actually make it. I'm glad it happened though.

My trips to Nagallapuram was with the closest of you people and I will always hold it close to me.

I also had fun with our numerous visits to the beach and restaurants. I always felt like that strengthened

our ever-growing bond.

 

Then came the dreadful day on which we had to split into separate batches. I was gradually okay with it,

as I had the chance to meet some new friends, with whom I eventually became closer to. It was with them

that I embarked upon my first project to, and it is with them that I am currently taking breaks with.

 

There comes a time in everyone's life where they have to take step in another direction, eventhough some will

think it is not the right decision. At moments like these, listen to what your heart says and decide based on

your instincts. Only you know what is right for you and what makes you happy. Always prioritize happiness and

relationships over success and wealth. I wish for all of you to be successful in whatever you choose to do,

and hope that we cross paths professionally or personally somewhere down the road.

 

Unfortunately, I cannot address everyone individually here, eventhough I so badly want to. I wish 

we had spent more time together, I have so many things left unsaid. But I'm going to stop here as

I reminisce and decide that I'm elated that it happened and not gloomy that it has end.

 

                THANK YOU ALL FOR BEING A PART OF MY LIFE. KEEP IN TOUCH.

                                                            

P.S. This message is BCCed to the people I care about.

 

XOXO

Vishal Rathnam JK

+91-9543571150

vishalrathnamspr@gmail.com
